Former Deputy Minister of Finance, Mcebisi Jonas, will on Friday be cross-examined by the legal team of Fana Hlongwane and Duduzane Zuma at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture in Parktown, Johannesburg. On Thursday, former Minister of Finance, Nhlanhla Nene, said efforts by the Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) to discredit him before his appearance before the Commission in 2018 may relate to their failed attempts to influence his final decision of placing VBS Bank under curatorship. Watch proceedings below: 